---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Cambly vs Preply: Which Platform Is Better in 2026?" description="Compare Cambly and Preply online tutoring platforms. Find the best choice for your English learning goals, budget, and preferred tutor type.">
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <div class="mb-6">
      <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wide">Platform Comparison</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Cambly vs Preply: Which Platform Is Better in 2026?</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg mb-8">Two popular online tutoring platforms, two very different approaches. We break down the key differences so you can choose the right fit.</p>

    <div class="bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-emerald-800 mb-2">Our Verdict</h2>
      <p class="text-emerald-700"><strong>Preply wins</strong> for learners who want structured, professional tutoring with personalized lesson plans. <strong>Cambly wins</strong> for casual learners who want unlimited, on-demand conversation practice with native speakers.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-10">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="border p-3 text-left">Feature</th>
            <th class="border p-3 text-left">Cambly</th>
            <th class="border p-3 text-left">Preply</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="border p-3 font-semibold">Starting Price</td><td class="border p-3">$9.99/month</td><td class="border p-3">$10/month</td></tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="border p-3 font-semibold">Tutor Type</td><td class="border p-3">Native speakers (volunteer tutors)</td><td class="border p-3">Certified professional tutors</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="border p-3 font-semibold">Class Format</td><td class="border p-3">Conversational, on-demand</td><td class="border p-3">Structured 1-on-1 lessons</td></tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="border p-3 font-semibold">Scheduling</td><td class="border p-3">Book instantly (talk anytime)</td><td class="border p-3">Book ahead with preferred tutors</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="border p-3 font-semibold">Lesson Plans</td><td class="border p-3">Limited to conversation topics</td><td class="border p-3">Personalized curriculum</td></tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="border p-3 font-semibold">Trial</td><td class="border p-3">7 days free</td><td class="border p-3">First lesson free</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="border p-3 font-semibold">Languages</td><td class="border p-3">15+ languages</td><td class="border p-3">50+ languages</td></tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="border p-3 font-semibold">Mobile App</td><td class="border p-3">Yes</td><td class="border p-3">Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="border p-3 font-semibold">Certificates</td><td class="border p-3">No</td><td class="border p-3">Completion certificates</td></tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="border p-3 font-semibold">Best For</td><td class="border p-3">Casual conversation practice</td><td class="border p-3">Focused skill development</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How Cambly and Preply Work</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">Cambly is built around spontaneous conversation. Once you log in, you can connect instantly with an available native English speaker through the Talk anytime feature. No scheduling required. Tutors on Cambly are not necessarily trained teachers; they are native speakers who want to practice conversation with language learners. Sessions are informal and focused on natural speaking practice.</p>
    <p class="mb-6">Preply takes a more traditional tutoring approach. You browse tutor profiles, read reviews, and book sessions with tutors you choose. Most Preply tutors hold teaching certifications and offer structured lessons tailored to your goals. Preply also provides a learning hub with resources to supplement your live sessions.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Who Wins: Cambly or Preply?</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">The answer depends entirely on what you are looking for:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Choose Cambly</strong> if you want unlimited conversation practice without planning. It is best for building confidence and getting comfortable with natural spoken English.</li>
      <li><strong>Choose Preply</strong> if you need a professional tutor who can build a structured plan around your goals. Preply is better for business English, exam prep, and serious learners.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Pros and Cons</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-10">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Cambly</h3>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-semibold mb-2">Pros:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-sm space-y-1 text-gray-700">
          <li>Unlimited talk anytime sessions</li>
          <li>No scheduling required</li>
          <li>Native English speakers</li>
          <li>Affordable monthly subscription</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-red-700 font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">Cons:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-sm space-y-1 text-gray-700">
          <li>No structured lesson plans</li>
          <li>Tutors are not certified teachers</li>
          <li>No progress tracking or certificates</li>
          <li>Conversation quality varies by tutor</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Preply</h3>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-semibold mb-2">Pros:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-sm space-y-1 text-gray-700">
          <li>Professional certified tutors</li>
          <li>Personalized lesson plans</li>
          <li>Progress tracking and certificates</li>
          <li>Flexible booking with favorite tutors</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-red-700 font-semibold mt-3 mb-2">Cons:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-sm space-y-1 text-gray-700">
          <li>Requires scheduling in advance</li>
          <li>Per-lesson costs add up</li>
          <li>Quality depends on tutor choice</li>
          <li>No unlimited conversation option</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The Bottom Line</h2>
    <p class="mb-6">Cambly and Preply serve different needs. If you want a casual, affordable way to practice conversation with native speakers whenever you have time, Cambly delivers. If you want a professional tutor who can build a structured path toward your language goals, Preply is the stronger choice.</p>

    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-teal-600 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8 text-center">
      <p class="text-white text-lg mb-4">Want to try a platform that combines AI convenience with human expertise?</p>
      <a href="/go/see-guru?aff=SG-SUAG151" class="inline-block bg-white text-emerald-700 font-bold px-8 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-100 transition">Try See Guru Free</a>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-10">
      <a href="/reviews/cambly/" class="block bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-4 hover:shadow-lg transition border">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-emerald-700">Read Our Full Cambly Review</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Pricing, features, and user ratings</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/reviews/preply/" class="block bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-4 hover:shadow-lg transition border">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-emerald-700">Read Our Full Preply Review</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Pricing, features, and user ratings</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 mb-10">
      <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Is Cambly better than Preply for beginners?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">Cambly is often easier for true beginners because you can start talking immediately without planning. Preply requires you to communicate your goals to a tutor before each session, which can be challenging if you are still building basic vocabulary.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Can I use both Cambly and Preply together?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">Yes. Many learners use Cambly for daily casual practice and Preply for weekly structured lessons. This combination can accelerate progress by mixing conversational exposure with professional guidance.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Which platform is more affordable?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">Cambly is more affordable for unlimited use. Its monthly subscription covers unlimited talk anytime sessions. Preply charges per lesson, which can be more expensive but offers more professional instruction.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Do both platforms offer mobile apps?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">Yes. Both Cambly and Preply have apps for iOS and Android, allowing you to practice or attend lessons from your phone or tablet.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Which is better for business English?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">Preply is generally better for business English because you can select tutors who specialize in business communication. You can discuss your industry and goals with the same tutor over multiple sessions.</p>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 pt-4 border-t">
      <p><strong>Affiliate Disclosure:</strong> LearnEnglish.Life may earn a commission when you sign up through links on this page, at no extra cost to you. This helps us keep the site free.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

